#: src/platform/releases/release-notes.tsx
msgid "<0>App Health Check</0>: Added a health check feature to the admin panel. Now shows real-time status and key metrics. <1>Environment Variables</1>: Admin panel now has read-only access to environment variables. Better transparency, easier config management."
msgstr "<0>App Health Check</0>: Added a health check feature to the admin panel. Now shows real-time status and key metrics. <1>Environment Variables</1>: Admin panel now has read-only access to environment variables. Better transparency, easier config management."

#. js-lingui-id: pQcyVv
#: src/platform/releases/release-notes.tsx
msgid "<0>Edit Kanban Stages:</0> You can now edit Kanban stages directly from the app, not just from the settings. This makes it easier to manage and customize your workflow on the fly. <1>\"No Value\" Column:</1> Cards that are not assigned to a specific value will now appear in a \"No Value\" column. This column can be shown or hidden as needed, ensuring no cards are overlooked."
msgstr "<0>Edit Kanban Stages:</0> You can now edit Kanban stages directly from the app, not just from the settings. This makes it easier to manage and customize your workflow on the fly. <1>\"No Value\" Column:</1> Cards that are not assigned to a specific value will now appear in a \"No Value\" column. This column can be shown or hidden as needed, ensuring no cards are overlooked."

#. js-lingui-id: cCqojY
#: src/platform/releases/release-notes.tsx
msgid "<0>Quick Access to Records</0>: Side panel lets you view and edit records without leaving your current page. <1>Keyboard Navigation</1>: Navigate the side panel with keyboard for better accessibility and faster workflows. <2>Pinned Actions</2>: More actions now displayed directly in the navbar for easier access."
msgstr "<0>Quick Access to Records</0>: Side panel lets you view and edit records without leaving your current page. <1>Keyboard Navigation</1>: Navigate the side panel with keyboard for better accessibility and faster workflows. <2>Pinned Actions</2>: More actions now displayed directly in the navbar for easier access."

